QUIZNAME: Direct & Indirect Proportion
SUBJECT: Maths
YEAR: 8

KEY: Direct proportion = When one value increases, the other increases at the same rate
KEY: Inverse proportion = When one value increases, the other decreases
KEY: Constant = A number that does not change
KEY: Workers = People doing a job together
KEY: Speed = Distance travelled per unit of time

Q: If y is directly proportional to x and x doubles, what happens to y?
A: It halves
A: It stays the same
CA: It doubles
A: It becomes zero

Q: 6 workers finish a job in 10 days. How long for 12 workers?
A: 20 days
A: 10 days
A: 8 days
CA: 5 days
